   SCOTUS-DEATH-PENALTY (Washington) _ The death penalty kept the
Supreme Court working late this week. Twice the justices responded
to the pleas of death row inmates, hours away from execution, not
only by granting last-minute stays of execution but also by
accepting their cases for full argument and decision. A news
analysis. By Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
