<SLUG> BC-ITALY-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT LOOKS LIKE THE LUNCH MENU, BUT IT'S YOUR CHILD'S REPORT CARD 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089) 
(bl) 
 By ALESSANDRA STANLEY   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROME _ The first parents meeting of the year at my child's
Italian public school started off with a warning. We all hunched
anxiously over tiny first-grade desks as the teacher rose from her
chair and stated solemnly, ``I have bad news.''
