r s BC-BKN-ATL-CAPS-COX     10-30 0880
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-ATL-CAPS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NBA capsules
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Dengerg
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTIC DIVISION
</P>
<P>
   MIAMI HEAT
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 33-17, eliminated in first round of playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Pat Riley, 5th season with Heat, 191-105; 17th season
overall, 947-404.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Tim James (25th), Rodney Buford (53rd);
free agents _ Anthony Carter, Harold Jamison, Otis Thorpe.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Terry Porter (Spurs), Terry Mills (Detroit)
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Keith Askins, P.J. Brown, Duane Causwell, Tim Hardaway,
Voshon Lenard, Dan Majerle, Jamal Mashburn, Alonzo Mourning, Mark
Strickland, Clarence Weatherspoon, Rex Walters.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Riley said he kept the Heat intact because he likes
his players. The truth, however, is that he was unable to get the
shooting guard he needs because he refused to part with talent.
Playoffs will tell the tale.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK KNICKS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 27-23, eliminated in NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Jeff Van Gundy, 5th season, 140-97.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Free agents _ Andrew Lang and John Wallace.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Herb Williams.
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Rick Brunson, Marcus Camby, Chris Childs, Chris Dudley,
Patrick Ewing, Allan Houston, Larry Johnson, Latrell Sprewell, Kurt
Thomas, Charlie Ward, Herb Williams.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Ewing's absence with Achilles woes is open-ended. The
big question is how the quick-striking Knicks adjust to him when he
returns. This team is not a major contender if it can't develop a
useful center.
</P>
<P>
   NEW JERSEY NETS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 16-34, missed playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Don Casey, 1st full season with Nets; 13-17 in 1998-99;
3rd season overall, 54-102.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Evan Eschmeyer (34th); trade _ Johnny
Newman; free agent _ Sherman Douglas.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Rony Seikaly, Eric Murdock (L.A. Clippers), Doug Overton
(Philadelphia).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Scott Burrell, Jamie Feick, Kendall Gill, Lucious
Harris, Kerry Kittles, Stephon Marbury, Jim McIlvaine, Eric
Murdock, Gheorghe Muresan, Elliot Perry, Keith Van Horn, Jayson
Williams.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Williams is out until January, and Kittles is slow in
his recovery from minor knee surgery. Still, the Nets are strong up
front and have firepower in Marbury and Gill. With good health,
they could get back to the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA 76ers
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 28-22, eliminated in second round of playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Larry Brown, 3rd season with Sixers, 58-74; 16th season
overall, 682-554.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Todd MacCulloch (47th); trade _ Jumaine
Jones, Billy Owens; free agent _ Bruce Bowen.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Harvey Grant (Orlando), Anthony Parker (Orlando).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Matt Geiger, Tyrone Hill, Larry Hughes, Allen Iverson,
Aaron McKie, Nazr Mohammed, Theo Ratliff, Eric Snow, George Lynch.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: A dearth of perimeter shooting will slow the 76ers'
progress. With center Theo Ratliff sidelined early with an injury,
the Sixers might not be able to win 56 percent of their games again
this season.
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON CELTICS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 19-31, missed playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Rick Pitino, 3rd year with Celtics, 55-77; 5th season
overall, 145-151.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Trades -- Danny Fortson (Denver), Eric Washington
(Denver), Eric Williams (Denver); free agents -- Calbert Cheaney,
Adrian Griffin.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Popeye Jones (Denver), Ron Mercer (Denver), Dwayne
Schintzius (Denver).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Kenny Anderson, Dana Barros, Tony Battie, Pervis
Ellison, Walter McCarty, Greg Minor, Vitaly Potapenko, Antoine
Walker.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: This is a deeper and more mobile Celtics team than
the one that disappointed last season. But unless Potapenko is much
improved, it's tough to see Boston as more than a fringe playoff
contender.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON WIZARDS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 18-32, missed playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Gar Heard 1st year, 0-0; 2nd year overall, 7-17.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft -- Richard Hamilton (7th), Calvin Booth
(35th); trade -- Ike Austin; free agent -- Aaron Williams.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Calbert Cheaney (Boston), Otis Thorpe (Miami), Terry
Davis (Orlando), Tim Legler.
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Juwan Howard, Randell Jackson, Tracy Murray, Mitch
Richmond, Rod Strickland, Otis Thorpe, Jahidi White, Chris Whitney,
Lorenzo Williams
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Some nice additions -- Hamilton, Austin and Aaron
Williams -- will make the Wizards respectable. But Strickland and
Richmond are coming off uneven seasons. This team improves only if
they play very well.
</P>
<P>
   ORLANDO MAGIC
</P>
<P>
   _ Last season: 33-17, eliminated in first round of playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Glenn ``Doc'' Rivers, 1st season with Magic; 1st
overall.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Trade -- Tariq Abdul-Wahad, Louis Bullock, Terry
Davis, Pat Garrity, Chris Gatling, Armen Gilliam, Corey Maggette,
