<P>
   N capsules
</P>
<P>
   PACIFIC DIVISION
</P>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES LAKERS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last year: 31-19, eliminated in second round of the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Phil Jackson, first season with the Lakers, 545-193
overall.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Devean George (23rd), John Celestand
(30th); trade _ A.C. Green; free agents _ Ron Harper, John Salley.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Ruben Patterson (Seattle), J.R. Reid (Milwaukee), Sean
Rooks (Dallas), Derek Harper (Detroit).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Kobe Bryant, Derek Fisher Rick Fox, Robert Horry, Sam
Jacobson, Travis Knight, Tyronn Lue, Shaquille O'Neal, Glen Rice.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: Can they figure out the triple-post offense? Will it
work without Michael Jordan? Stay tuned. There's enough talent here
to win the whole thing, with savvy Jackson goading O'Neal to have
his finest season.
</P>
<P>
   PORTLAND TRAIL BLAZERS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last year: 35-15, eliminated in third round of the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Mike Dunleavy, third year with the Blazers, 81-51;
eighth year overall, 289-345.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Trade _ Roberto Bergersen, Scottie Pippen, Steve
Smith; free agents _ Joe Kleine, Detlef Schrempf.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Jim Jackson (Atlanta), Isaiah Rider (Atlanta).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Greg Anthony, Brian Grant, Gary Grant, Jermaine O'Neal,
Arvydas Sabonis, Damon Stoudamire, Rasheed Wallace, Bonzi Wells,
Stacey Augmon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: If it looks too good to be true: Smith's knees,
Pippen's refusal to step up without M.J. and the problems of
keeping so many talented guys happy are real obstacles as the
Blazers try to make it to the Finals.
</P>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO KINGS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last year: 27-23, eliminated in first round of the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Rick Adelman, second season with the Kings, 27-23; 10th
year overall, 384-275.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Ryan Robertson (45th); trade _ Nick
Anderson; free agents _ Tyrone Corbin, Tony Delk, Darrick Martin,
Bill Wennington.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gone: Vernon Maxwell (Seattle), Oliver Miller (Phoenix), Tariq
Abdul-Wahad (Orlando).
</P>
<P>
   _ Back: Jon Barry, Vlade Divac, Lawrence Funderburke, Scot
Pollard, Predrag Stojakovic, Chris Webber, Jason Williams; Corliss
Williamson.
</P>
<P>
   _ Outlook: The Kings are the new darlings of the NBA. TNT and
NBC love exciting young point guard Williams. Adelman expertly
guided them to a rare playoff berth. The hard part is doing it
again and improving.
</P>
<P>
   PHOENIX SUNS
</P>
<P>
   _ Last year: 27-23, eliminated in first round of playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Coach: Danny Ainge, third season as coach of the Suns, 122-83.
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: Draft _ Shawn Marion, (9th) overall); trade _
Anfernee Hardaway; free agents _ Oliver Miller, Rodney Rogers,
