Buford, Ga., plumber, dreamed up the ``Tupperware party.'' Divorced
and driven, Wise was the first woman ever on the cover of Business
Week (april 1954) and was a pretty colorful character. For the
topsales women, she would bury diamond rings, mink coats, and toy
Cadillacs (exchangable for real ones) on the grounds of her estate
near Kissimmee, Fla., and hand out shovels. (Dart, Cox News
