<P>
   GUATEMALA-ELECTIONS _ GUATEMALA CITY, Guatemala _ Guatemala's
shakey hold on peace will be tested Nov. 7, when the country holds
its first presidential election since the 1995 peace accords ended
the 36-year civil war. Public interest in the election seems low,
despite the fact that one of the major candidates ? a guy whose
nickname is ``The Gruff Chicken'' ? recently admitted murdering two
men years ago while he lived in Mexico, a crime for which he was
never prosecuted. We profile the candidates and the country's
efforts to find stability after decades of war. (Williams, Cox News
Service).
