<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   COELHO _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore bragged about the
``higher standards'' of his campaign finance apparatus in his first
nationally televised appearance with challenger Bill Bradley in New
Hampshire last week. But at the top of Gore's campaign
organizational pyramid sits Tony Coelho, an former California
congressman who some critics say helped usher in the era of ``big
money'' in politics that Gore vowed to ``fight my heart out'' to
end if elected president. (Shepard and Malone 1100&AMP;add.)
