<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 1030: HOSTAGE CRISIS ANNIVERSARY _ For Iranians,
the takeover of the U.S. Embassy 20 years ago this week is their
Bunker Hill; their Boston Tea Party. It galvanized their
revolutionary fervor as they took on the ``Den of Spies'' that had
helped install and support the brutal, dictatorial Shah. Today in
Iran, the takeover highlights the country's identity crisis.
(Kaplow, Cox News Service) Art includes 2-column color photo of the
former embassy, a 4-column color photo of a woman walking along the
graffiti-covered sidewalk, a 2-column color photo of graffiti and a
2-column color photo of the U.S. seal on the embassy wall and
1-column photo of former hostage-taker.
