<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-COLTS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS SAY COLTS HAVE POTENTIAL TO FOLLOW THEIR TREK TO GLORY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Emmitt Smith wasn't thinking ``Triplets'' when he joined the
Cowboys in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   Troy Aikman was coming off a rookie season in which he was 0-11
as a starter. Michael Irvin, who had appeared in 20 games (4-16) at
that point, brought 58 career receptions for slightly more than
1,000 yards into '90.
</P>
<P>
   Smith instead took note of what Barry Sanders was doing in
Detroit, what Neil Anderson was doing in Chicago and what Thurman
Thomas was doing in Buffalo.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was the elite group that I wanted to be in. This was what
I myself wanted to do on a year-to-year basis,'' Smith said this
week. ``I wasn't even thinking of \Rhelping to create a triplets
concept on the Cowboys\S in that regard.''
</P>
<P>
   While the comparison between ``Old Triplets'' and ``New
Triplets'' is inevitable with rookie running back Edgerrin James
joining second-year quarterback Peyton Manning and fourth-year wide
receiver Marvin Harrison in Indianapolis, where the Cowboys play
the Colts today, one fact remains:
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, Indianapolis has some young players who remind a
lot of people of our offensive group back several years ago,''
Aikman said. ``And, yes, I think they've got the potential to be
that. But as soon as I say, `Yes, I think they do,' then I'm
implying that it's easy to do and that it just happens.
</P>
<P>
   ``And I know that's not the case.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys won Super Bowls in three of four seasons (1992-93,
'95); Aikman was a fourth-, fifth- and seventh-year NFL
quarterback. That means for the Indy Triplets to match what the
Dallas Triplets have done, Manning-Harris-James would have to win
Super Bowls in 2001, 2002 and 2004.
</P>
<P>
   ``Over a period of time ... that's the whole key,'' Smith said.
``That has been the unique thing about what Michael, Troy, myself
and this whole organization have been able to do. Over a 10-year
period, we've been fairly consistent.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's what I strive for as an individual. I knew from Day One
that I'd rather average a certain amout of yards over a long period
of time than go out and have one great year and eight to 10
mediocre years.
</P>
<P>
   ``Consistency is what we've strived for. I think we've been able
to sustain it.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys are 87-59 (.596) with Aikman as the starting
quarterback, 98-62 (.613) including postseason games.
</P>
<P>
   Irvin, who is the oldest Cowboys' Triplet at 33, now faces a
career decision about his future since an examination for an Oct.
10 spinal contusion revealed a genetic narrowing of the spinal
canal called cervical stenosis. The Cowboys are 36-11 in games in
which Irvin has 100 yards or more receiving.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys are 48-10 when Smith rushed for 100 yards or more in
a game, 55-10 including the postseason.
</P>
<P>
   And when Irvin and Smith both eclipse the 100-yard mark in the
same game, the Cowboys are 20-0, 23-0 including the postseason.
</P>
<P>
   While comparisons among sports groups or individuals generally
are unfair for both sides, Aikman was able to say:
</P>
<P>
   ``With Manning coming in last year and showing what he already
has shown, and with James being a top rookie and Harrison being
very productive ... the comparison is probably a little more valid
in this case.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
