<SLUG> BC-FBC-GAFLA-LOCKERROOM-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Georgia's air attack didn't get off the ground
 &HT;    By John Manasso
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSONVILLE _ Georgia had the running game necessary to beat
Florida. But it didn't have the passing game.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs, who entered with a rushing attack averaging 176
yards per game, totaled 155. In the 1990s, the Gators have allowed
opponents to rush for more than 100 yards only 20 times. The Gators
have lost 16 of those games.
</P>
<P>
   But Georgia got poor performances from quarterback Quincy Carter
and the offensive line. Carter completed just 6 of 23 passes for 76
yards, no touchdowns and one interception. He was chased around the
backfield all game and took several heavy hits.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs partly blamed the heavy rain that fell throughout
the game, but mostly they blamed themselves.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Florida) kept a pretty good pass rush on me,'' Carter said.
``They were coming from pretty much everywhere. We got outplayed.
There's pretty much no other way to describe it.''
</P>
<P>
   After an impressive three-play, 38-second scoring drive on the
its opening possession, Georgia struggled mightily.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't just totally blame it on the pass rush,'' said
Carter, who set career highs against the Gators last year by
connecting on 33 of 49 passes for 368 yards. ``I wasn't totally in
sync, either. I got rocked a little bit. It's our team. Our offense
wasn't clicking in the second half. That's the bottom line.''
</P>
<P>
   In that second half, the Bulldogs did not complete their first
pass until less than 14 minutes remained. In the second half,
Carter was 2-of-10 for 21 yards.
</P>
<P>
   A key play came with 9:20 left in the third quarter when
starting left tackle Alex Jennings went out with a sprained right
ankle. He did not return. Playing in his stead was freshman George
Foster, meaning that along with right tackle Jon Stinchcomb, the
Bulldogs had freshmen at both tackle positions.
</P>
<P>
   ``The weather was kind of a problem; then again, we lost one of
our top linemen,'' running back Patrick Pass said. ``We were
playing out there with a couple of freshmen, and it's hard to play
against a Florida team with freshmen. And you've got to give credit
to Alex Brown. He had a great game.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Carter) can't do it all. We've got to protect him more than
we did.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
